cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.MM

This paper deals with interference management in device-to-device (D2D) communications underlaying cellular networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a pricing framework and formulates a Stackelberg game, indicating a possible fit with cs.GT (Game Theory). Additionally, the paper discusses power allocation strategies and analyzes competition among D2D users, suggesting a possible fit with cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SI (Signal Processing). Finally, the paper conducts simulations to verify the proposed framework, indicating a possible fit with cs.MM (Multimedia).
